Public Employees Retirement System of Ohio Has $7,518,000 Position in Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. (NASDAQ:BECN)

					Posted by Danessa Lincoln on Jul 18th, 2017 // No Comments 




Public Employees Retirement System of Ohio continued to hold its position in shares of  Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. (NASDAQ:BECN) during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 152,937 shares of the company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Public Employees Retirement System of Ohio owned about 0.25% of Beacon Roofing Supply worth $7,518,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. BlackRock Inc. increased its position in  Beacon Roofing Supply by 80,484.5% in the first quarter. BlackRock Inc. now owns 4,021,973 shares of the company’s stock worth $197,720,000 after buying an additional 4,016,982 shares in the last quarter.  Norges Bank bought a new position in  Beacon Roofing Supply during the fourth quarter worth $23,112,000.  BlueCrest Capital Management Ltd bought a new position in  Beacon Roofing Supply during the first quarter worth $21,690,000.  Vanguard Group Inc. increased its position in  Beacon Roofing Supply by 5.4% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 4,845,530 shares of the company’s stock worth $238,207,000 after buying an additional 246,233 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, MUFG Securities EMEA plc bought a new position in  Beacon Roofing Supply during the first quarter worth $8,849,000. 


 Get Beacon Roofing Supply Inc. alerts:



Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. (NASDAQ:BECN) traded down 0.87% during midday trading on Tuesday, hitting $47.67. 154,599 shares of the stock traded hands. The firm has a market cap of $2.87 billion, a P/E ratio of 29.08 and a beta of 1.33. Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. has a 1-year low of $39.50 and a 1-year high of $52.12. The company has a 50-day moving average price of $48.82 and a 200-day moving average price of $47.60. 




Beacon Roofing Supply (NASDAQ:BECN) last posted its earnings results on Thursday, May 4th. The company reported ($0.04) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of ($0.06) by $0.02. The firm had revenue of $870.70 million during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $814.74 million. Beacon Roofing Supply had a net margin of 2.37% and a return on equity of 9.42%. The company’s revenue was up 5.7% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the company earned $0.03 earnings per share.  Analysts predict that  Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. will post $2.37 EPS for the current year. 
