Beacon Roofing Supply - Wikipedia





















 






Beacon Roofing Supply

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article is an orphan, as no other articles link to it. Please introduce links to this page from related articles; try the Find link tool for suggestions. (August 2013)



Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc.


Type

Public


Industry
Building Materials


Founded
1928


Headquarters
Herndon, Virginia, United States



Key people

Paul Isabella (President and CEO), Robert Buck
Chairman of the Board


Revenue
 US$4.1 Billion (FY 2016)[1]



Operating income

US$ 204,984 million (FY 2016)



Net income

 US$ 89,917 million (FY 2016)[2]



Number of employees

5,000 (2016)[3]


Website
www.beaconroofingsupply.com


Beacon Roofing Supply, Inc. (NASDAQ: BECN) is an American publicly traded company which sells residential and non-residential roofing products, as well as related building products in North America. The company currently consist of 13 regional companies in 48 states and 6 Canadian Provinces, 384 locations and over 5,000 employees.[4] In addition to roofing, local divisions may also sell windows, siding, decking, waterproofing, and other external building products. [5][6] The company is currently headquartered in Herndon, Virginia.[7]



Contents


1 Regional brands
2 Company History
3 Executive profiles
4 References
5 External links



Regional brands[edit]
Beacon Roofing Supply consists of the following companies:[8]

Alabama Roofing Supply
Atlantic Building Products
